DATABASE CASCADE RELATIONSHIPS MAP
====================================
Format: PARENT_TABLE (action) → CHILD_TABLES (cascade behavior)
All foreign keys include ON UPDATE CASCADE unless explicitly noted.

[TEACHERS]
teachers.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  ├─ classes.teacher_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ timetable.teacher_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ agent_sessions.teacher_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ exam_papers.teacher_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ exam_uploads.teacher_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ grading_blueprints.teacher_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ generated_exams.teacher_id (CASCADE)
  └─ user_email_credentials.user_id (CASCADE)

[CLASSES]
classes.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  ├─ uploads.class_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ student_class.class_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ flags.class_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ timetable.class_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ attendance.class_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ exam_types.class_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ agent_sessions.class_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ exam_papers.class_id (CASCADE)
  └─ grading_sessions.class_id (CASCADE)

[STUDENTS]
students.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  ├─ student_class.student_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ flags.student_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ attendance.student_id (CASCADE)
  ├─ grades.student_id (CASCADE)
  └─ grading_sessions.student_id (CASCADE)

[EXAM TYPES]
exam_types.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  ├─ grades.exam_type_id (CASCADE)
  └─ grading_sessions.exam_type_id (CASCADE)

[EXAM PAPERS]
exam_papers.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  └─ grading_blueprints.exam_paper_id (SET NULL on DELETE, CASCADE on UPDATE)
     Note: Blueprint survives paper deletion. Only the display reference is cleared.

[EXAM UPLOADS]
exam_uploads.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  └─ grading_sessions.exam_upload_id (CASCADE)

[GRADING BLUEPRINTS]
grading_blueprints.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  └─ grading_sessions.blueprint_id (CASCADE)

[GRADING SESSIONS]
grading_sessions.id (DELETE/UPDATE) →
  └─ grading_question_results.session_id (CASCADE)

[JUNCTION / LEAF TABLES (No downstream cascades)]
- student_class (links classes ↔ students)
- uploads
- flags
- timetable
- attendance
- grades
- agent_sessions
- grading_question_results
- generated_exams
- processing_jobs
- user_email_credentials

NOTES:
- ON UPDATE CASCADE is applied to ALL foreign keys. Primary key changes (rare) will propagate automatically.
- ON DELETE CASCADE means child rows are permanently removed when the parent is deleted.
- ON DELETE SET NULL (exam_papers → grading_blueprints) preserves the blueprint but drops the paper reference.
- PostgreSQL enforces these constraints at the database level. SQLAlchemy's passive_deletes=True optimizes ORM behavior to rely entirely on DB cascades (no extra SELECT/DELETE queries).
- Deleting a root entity (Teacher/Class/Student) will recursively wipe all dependent records in a single DB transaction.